div.p:
(75) Moreover, if we saw that there was no such thing as any eternal nature to be seen,
   those who assert the liability of the world to destruction would not appear to be so guilty of disparaging the world without any excuse,
   since they would have no example whatever of anything being everlasting;

quote.foreign:
"Like leaves on trees the race of man is found,
Now green in youth, now withering on the ground;
Another race the following spring supplies;
